The paper deals with collision prediction and avoidance in the context of multi-agent systems, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO). The approach proposed involves the use of probabilistic bounds and criterion functions, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of policy-search approaches, which are often used in machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.CV).
